<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
Most of the published records of the species are from Western Australia, where the species inhabits Brigalow tropical savanna and Eastern Australian temperate forest habitats (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1071/IT9940299" author="Malipatil, MB" journalOrPublisher="Invertebrate Systematics" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" pagination="299 - 327" refId="B10" refString="Malipatil, MB, 1994. Revision of Australian Geocoris Fallen and Stylogeocoris Montandon (Heteroptera: Lygaeidae: Geocorinae). Invertebrate Systematics 8 (2): 299 - 327, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1071/IT9940299" title="Revision of Australian Geocoris Fallen and Stylogeocoris Montandon (Heteroptera: Lygaeidae: Geocorinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1071/IT9940299" volume="8" year="1994">Malipatil 1994</bibRefCitation>
). In the material deposited in the BPBM three specimens from the Central Range montane rain forests of New Guinea are present.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
Based on the specimens available as well as the original description and illustrations provided by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1071/IT9940299" author="Malipatil, MB" journalOrPublisher="Invertebrate Systematics" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" pagination="299 - 327" refId="B10" refString="Malipatil, MB, 1994. Revision of Australian Geocoris Fallen and Stylogeocoris Montandon (Heteroptera: Lygaeidae: Geocorinae). Invertebrate Systematics 8 (2): 299 - 327, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1071/IT9940299" title="Revision of Australian Geocoris Fallen and Stylogeocoris Montandon (Heteroptera: Lygaeidae: Geocorinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1071/IT9940299" volume="8" year="1994">Malipatil (1994)</bibRefCitation>
the species possesses a combination of characters diagnostic of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kobor" authorityYear="2019" class="Insecta" family="Geocoridae" genus="Umbrageocoris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Umbrageocoris" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Umbrageocoris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, including the presence of a median longitudinal furrow on vertex, a cup- or Y-shaped labial trough, and the arrangement of sutures of abdominal tergites 4/5 and 5/6. The following new combination is accordingly proposed: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kóbor" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Malipatil" baseAuthorityYear="1994" class="Insecta" family="Geocoridae" genus="Umbrageocoris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Umbrageocoris woodwardi" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="woodwardi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Umbrageocoris woodwardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Malipatil, 1994), comb. nov.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
